            "1st Ascension Passive": {
                "name": "Jade-Claimed Flower",
                "img": "https:\/\/static.wikia.nocookie.net\/gensin-impact\/images\/9\/95\/Talent_Jade-Claimed_Flower.png",
                "text": "If Hanega: Song of the Wind comes into contact with <span class=\"text-hydro\"><b>Hydro<\/b><\/span>\/<span class=\"text-pyro\"><b>Pyro<\/b><\/span>\/<span class=\"text-cryo\"><b>Cryo<\/b><\/span>\/<span class=\"text-electro\"><b>Electro<\/b><\/span> when it is unleashed, this instance of the Windfavored state will obtain buffs according to the contacted element(s):<ul><li><span class=\"text-hydro\"><b>Hydro<\/b><\/span>: Kuugoryoku Point cap increases by 20.<\/li><li><span class=\"text-pyro\"><b>Pyro<\/b><\/span>: ATK increases by 30%.<\/li><li><span class=\"text-cryo\"><b>Cryo<\/b><\/span>: CRIT Rate increases by 20%.<\/li><li><span class=\"text-electro\"><b>Electro<\/b><\/span>: When Normal and Charged Attacks hit an opponent, 0.8 Energy will be restored. Energy can be restored this way every 0.2s.<\/li><\/ul><br\/>You can have up to 2 different kinds of these buffs simultaneously."
            },
            "4th Ascension Passive": {
                "name": "Gales of Reverie",
                "img": "https:\/\/static.wikia.nocookie.net\/gensin-impact\/images\/4\/4f\/Talent_Gales_of_Reverie.png",
                "text": "When the Wanderer hits opponents with Kuugo: Fushoudan or Kuugo: Toufukai in his Windfavored state, he has a 16% chance to obtain the Descent effect: The next time the Wanderer accelerates in mid-air while in this instance of the Windfavored state, this effect will be removed, this acceleration instance will not consume any Kuugoryoku Points, and he will fire off 4 wind arrows that deal 35% of his ATK as <span class=\"text-anemo\"><b>Anemo DMG<\/b><\/span> each.<br\/>For each Kuugo: Fushoudan and Kuugo: Toufukai that does not produce this effect, the next attack of those types will have a 12% increased chance of producing it. The calculation of the effect production is done once every 0.1s."
            },
